<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9829062168727></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9829062168727><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=9829062168727>Erudites look so cool</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=9829062168727#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2387><span id= >Nazefein</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>11 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Feb 23rd 12:30 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am an inkie SK, but if I had to create my life over again id make it as an Erudite.&nbsp;&nbsp;Besides the sheer coolness (and they look SOOOOOO cool in their armor), they have tons of mana.  They're also so rare in the game that just being an Erudite SK is a reward in itself.  People will remember you, trust me.  <br><br>I definitely recommend thoroughly considering what points to put into your Erud Sk though.  Get that agi and dex to 75, then dump the rest in str.  Remember that there are now so much of a variety of items out there that can give bonuses to str, dex, and agi that you would be that far behind your larger SK brothers when it comes to dealing out damage.  Anyways, the way strength is figured in damage in EQ, the difference in an erudite SK with 100 str at level 30, for example, and an ogre SK with 150 str at level 30, MIGHT mean a difference of 5 10 points of damage per round.  <br><br>So take heed Erudites, use your brain to make up for your brawn, and ye shall be rewarded with endless power...<br><br>Nazefein T'Uzzra<br>41 SK <br>Luclin<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
