	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off this OGRE SK would like to say....play what you like...just that simple, me personally i like the ogre and could not imagine being any other race.<br><br>There are advantages and disadvantages to each race....and since I am an ogre i will tell you why i love the ogre<br><br>As an ogre SK i have more HP and str than the other races, I get the highest possible AC items and dont worry about STR or INT...as an ogre my STR is 175ish AC 850ish HP 1750ish at LVL 45.&nbsp;&nbsp;With these stats i am a fairly good tank...now you say WOW your a good tank but you sure cant cast can you??....Wrong i sure can. At lvl 45 I dont solo i group... with a clarity on me i can pull mobs, chain cast shadow vortex, shroud of pain, Heart Flutter, steal STR and what ever other spell i think i might need, kill the mob and go pull another one and with almost no down time(on my part anyway).<br><br>To me the tanking and str is much more important than the extra mana I get from INT when that can be compensated for with a clarity that you get from groups as an SK YOU should keep your casters alive...the War is not the best tank WE ARE...your cleric cast a CH and he is now getting the crap beat out of him can a War taunt off....no...cast a shadow vortex or heart flutter...bam...MOB on me...thats why in MY opinion you NEED all the AC and HP you can get...My high str is a bonus I love to hit in the 80's damage wise with my MOSS(mace of the shadowed soul) and to be able to wear my armor without getting encumbered =)<br><br>Gruz<br>45sk (karana)<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
