<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98424703967724></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98424703967724><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=98424703967724>RE: Why not Erud?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=98424703967724#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Mar 10th 12:57 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I'm still pretty low level, but I love my Eru SK.&nbsp;&nbsp;But even though she's young, I do have a bit of advice that's worth heeding:<br><br>PUT A LOT OF POINTS INTO STRENGTH!!!<br><br>I put about 7pts into intelligence, which may pay off, but she gets encumbered mighty quick.  She is wearing a full suit of armor, but it's leather . . . when she can afford it, she may not be able to wear the ringmail & steel, which is definitely going to be a problem.  This can be overcome if you don't do what I did and put more pts into strength, stamina, and all that good stuff.  I'd redo this character, but seeing as I've already put in a lot of time and grown a bit attached, I'll probably stick with her.  But learn from my mistake.<br><br>BTW, no one ever mentions how being intelligent also means that you can learn very quickly to use more than one melee style (1H blunt, 1H slash, & 2h slash) at low levels, which keeps things interesting.  Only thing is you still have to put a lot of pts into strength so you can carry your various weapons.  You will also learn to bash extremely quickly, and your taunt will quickly become irresistable.<br><br>Also, my SK hasn't got her spells yet, so the fact that she's weak hasn't kept her from doing quite well in pure melee attacks.  She can take on blues and kill them off before they get more than a bubble of hp.  So imagine what your Eru SK can do if you give her plenty of strength points.<br><br>Hope that helps,<br>Aanka<br>7 SK, Saryn Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
