<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98161253212709></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98161253212709><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=98161253212709>RE: Why not Erud?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=98161253212709#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 8th 6:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Don't listen to these people who give you this "3/4 warrior" BS.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you like being an erud sk, then that's all that matters.  If these "3/4" people are so worried about melee, then they should just be warriors and shut up.  The ability to cast spells is what defines an SK.  As a result, a good player can turn the erud sk's large mana pool into a decisive weapon.  <br><br>As far as strength goes, there are a multitude of items out there that allow you to boost STR to a decent level.  My DESK has a STR of 130 with siphon strength going.  I would recommend putting some bonus points into AGI to boost your AC as well.<br><br>There are no "good" or "bad" race/character classes.  The character is what you make of him/her.  If the game were bounded by strict formulas regarding character creation, then why bother?  Trolls and ogres are good in melee, but try casting those large mana cost spells later on.  At some point Mr. Ogre sk is gonna be low on mana and need to FD a few times and wish he was an erudite or an elf.<br><br>The only real drawback to erudites and humans that is not offset by an advantage is eyesight.  But you will get spells later on to fix that.<br><br>Just play the way you want and have fun...it's a game, for chrissakes.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
