	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 8th 6:21 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It is all about how YOU want your character to develop... if there was a decisively &#8220;best&#8221; race to play, then Verant would have done a poor job play-balancing.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Items abound that will allow you to grow in any direction you desire, but str is easier to increase than int.  Large races, with bonus HP, STR and STA will tank better.  Other races, with higher int will be more flexible, casting more and having a higher DEX for weapons that proc. [This is often overlooked at earlier levels, but becomes immensely powerful later.]<br><br>HOWEVER, if you choose Erudite as your race, be forewarned that your GREATEST stat strength (int) is inherently nerfed.  Hybrids do NOT get the full mana compliment that pure casters derive, from the same stat.  This penalty also holds true for items with a +XX mana quality... SKs only get a fraction of that total.  <br><br>I hope this aids any aspirant SKs out there.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
